wikipedia_page.main: John Beauchamp (20 October 1825 – 30 May 1911) was an English first-class cricketer active 1854–62 who played for Surrey. He was born in Chertsey and died in Greenham, Berkshire where he lived. He played in six first-class matches.

response: John Beauchamp or John de Beauchamp may refer to:
*John Beauchamp (MP for New Shoreham) (fl. 1330s–1340s), may well be the same person as the one above
*John Beauchamp, 1st Baron Beauchamp (fifth creation) (c. 1400–1475), nobleman and administrator
*John Beauchamp (Plymouth Company) (1592–1655), backer of the Plymouth Company
